Bonang Matheba was a vision in white as she kicked off the Grand White Dinner series in Cape Town on 24 February The event, which took place at the Jan van Riebeeck Sports Field, welcomed over 1 000 guests dressed in the traditional all-white attire. A memorable opening ceremony saw dozens of white doves released to mark the true meaning of the event – peace, love and unity. Musical acts performing on the day included Mafikizolo, Swing Collective and DJ Lloyd. Also taking to the stage with a magical performance were a few members of the South African National Circus.  READ MORE: Bonang’s book goes global – News24 Image: Instagram